ISTANBUL, Turkey, May 1â€”At least 39 persons were killed and about 200 wounded today when a giant May Day rally in the heart of Istanbul turned into a gun battle with ultraleftists pitted against the police and trade unionists.

Panic broke out as shots scattered crowd estimated at about 150,000 jammed into Taksim Square.

The police said the death toll was at least 35, and a check of hospitals later raised the number to 39. At least dozen people, including four policemen, were in critical condition at the hospitals.

Rooftop snipers exchanged fire with the police as people scrambled for cover, Cars went up in flames and exploded.

The windows of hotels, banks and office buildings around the square were shattered by bullets and rocks during two hours of disorders.